AMERICAN UNITED MUTUAL LIFE INSURANCE COMPANY et al., Creditors, Appellants, v. CITY OF AVON PARK, FLORIDA, Debtor, Appellee. No. 9294. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Jan. 31, 1940. Giles J. Patterson, of Jacksonville, Fla., Harry L. Thompson and Edgar John Phillips, both of Clearwater, Fla., for appellants. Robert J. Pleus, of Orlando, Fla., for appellee.

Before HUTCHESON, HOLMES, and McCORD, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

There being no substantial distinction between this case and that presented in Vallette v. City of Vero Beach, 5 Cir., 104 F.2d 59, the order appealed from is affirmed, upon the authority of that case.

Affirmed.
